Dear <%= @offer[:applicant][:first_name] %> <%= @offer[:applicant][:last_name] %>,

<%= @tab %>I am pleased to offer you an appointment as a Teaching Assistant in the Department of Computer Science. The starting date of your appointment will be <b><%= format_time(@offer[:start_date],1) %></b> and this appointment will end on <b><%= format_time(@offer[:end_date],1) %></b> with no further notice to you.

Your appointment will be for <b><%= '%.2f' % @offer[:hours] %></b> hours for <b><%= @offer[:position] %></b>, and your supervisor will be Professor <%= list_instructors(@offer[:instructors]) %>.  You will be paid $<%= '%.2f' % @offer[:session][:pay] %>/hour.  You will be paid in equal instalments, once per month for the period of your appointment. Your salary will be paid by direct deposit.  Your total salary is $<%= '%.2f' % (@offer[:session][:pay]* @offer[:hours]) %> plus 4% vacation pay  $<%= '%.2f' % (@offer[:session][:pay]* @offer[:hours]*0.04) %> for a total of  $<%= '%.2f' % ((@offer[:session][:pay]* @offer[:hours])+(@offer[:session][:pay]* @offer[:hours]*0.04)) %>.

This appointment is being granted on the basis that you are a student or Postdoctoral Fellow (PDF) at the University of Toronto on the starting date of the appointment and will remain eligible to work in the bargaining unit for the duration of the appointment. If you are not a student or PDF on the starting date of this appointment, this offer is revoked, deemed null and void and the University will have no obligations under this letter. If, during the period of this appointment, you should cease to be registered as a University of Toronto student for any reason other than convocation, or should your position as a PDF end, as the case may be, you must immediately notify your supervisor, and your appointment may immediately cease without any further obligations to you.

This appointment is also being granted on the condition that you are or will be legally authorized to work in Canada on the Starting Date and in particular will have a Social Insurance Number or the requisite Canadian government issued valid study permit ---and will present the originals of same to the Human Resources Department or Business Officer, upon request. If you are unable to satisfy this condition, this Offer Letter will be automatically deemed null and void. This appointment is also conditional upon your being able to attend on and perform your duties on campus as of the Starting Date, or no later than 1 month of the Starting Date. For clarity, in the event that some or all of your duties may be performed remotely, you are required to be situated within a geographical proximity that would allow for attendance on campus. If you will not be able to be on campus on the Starting Date, but will be able to do so within 1 month of the Starting Date, please advise your supervisor. If you are not able to satisfy this condition at all, then you will be deemed to have abandoned your employment and this Offer Letter will be deemed null and void.

Please note that the Government of Canada currently imposes a 14-day quarantine period for any person entering Canada from another country (subject to limited exemptions). As such, the University recommends you take this quarantine period into account when planning your arrival in Canada. Please consider arriving in Canada early enough so that there is sufficient time to quarantine and then attend at a Service Canada location to obtain a Social Insurance Number prior to the commencement of your employment.

As a Teaching Assistant, you will be a member of the Canadian Union of Public Employees (CUPE) Local 3902, Unit 1 bargaining unit.  Your employment will be governed by the terms and conditions of the collective agreement between the University of Toronto and CUPE Local 3902, which may be found on the web at:

<%= @tab %><%= set_link("https://hrandequity.utoronto.ca/agreements/#cupe3902_unit1")%>

A statement about the Union prepared by the Union, along with other information about the Union, including information about the Trans Fund, Survivors Fund, International Workers’ Fund, Childcare Fund, Healthcare Plan Funds, Research Assistants’ Fund, Tuition Assistance and Funding Top-Up Funds available to employees from the Union, can be found at <%= set_link("http://www.cupe3902.org/unit-1/", "here")%>. All of this information is that of the Union, represents the views of the Union and has not been approved or endorsed by the University.

<u>Mandatory Training</u>

You are required to take the following mandatory training. You must complete this training within 60 days of hire.


<%= @tab %> 1. Basic Occupational Health and Safety Awareness Training Program provided by the Office of Environmental Health and Safety available at <%= set_link("https://ehs.utoronto.ca/basic-health-and-safety-training/")%>. You can seek an exemption from the above mandatory health & safety training by providing your previous training documentation to Environmental Health & Safety at ehs.courses@utoronto.ca or by calling 416-978-4467.

<%= @tab %> 2. U of T AODA Online Training, provided by the Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act (AODA) Office, available at <%= set_link("http://aoda.hrandequity.utoronto.ca/")%>.

You will be notified by email when the training module becomes available for your completion, normally one month after the start date of this appointment. You can seek an exemption from the mandatory AODA training by emailing your previous training documentation to aoda@utoronto.ca.

Please note that you only need to take the above training programs once with the University (although you may need to retake one or both training programs if they are updated or amended). If you have already taken one or both of these training programs, please confirm with your supervisor. In addition to informing your supervisor, you must also provide the required documentation to the contacts specified above if you have not previously done so.

Completion of this training will be automatically captured in the system and you will be paid for this training in accordance with the rates set out in your collective agreement.

If this is your first appointment after becoming a Ph.D. student, you will be guaranteed five more appointments of the same number of hours in subsequent years as per Article 16.06 of the CUPE 3902 (Unit 1) Collective Agreement. If this is not your first appointment, you may still be owed one or more subsequent
appointments under the aforementioned Article. If this is the case, you may consult the letter you received last April, where your appointment status was summarized. Please feel free to contact <%= ENV['TA_COORD']%> to see how various guarantees fit together.

You should contact your supervisor as soon as possible to discuss any questions you have about your duties. You will soon be given the opportunity to review the Description of Duties and Allocation of Hours (DDAH) form, which will set out more specifically the duties of your position, and the hours assigned to each.

Please sign below to indicate your acceptance of this offer, and return a copy of this letter to me as soon as possible but no later than 2 days after you have been provided with the DDAH form. If we have not heard from you by this deadline, this offer may be withdrawn. If you are unable to accept this offer, please advise me immediately.

By signing this letter, I understand and accept the above Teaching Assistantship for <%= @offer[:position] %> on the above-noted terms and conditions and understand and agree that the offer will be deemed null and void (or my employment will be deemed abandoned) if any of the above noted conditions are not satisfied.

If you have any questions, please contact <%= ENV['TA_COORD']%> at tacoord@cs.toronto.edu.
